00778 #ifdef DD_VERBOSE

00802 int
00803 cuddGarbageCollectZdd(
00804   DdManager * unique,
00805   int  clearCache)
00806 {
00807     DdCache     *cache = unique->cache;
00808 #ifdef __osf__
00809 #pragma pointer_size save
00810 #pragma pointer_size short
00811 #endif
00812     DdNode      **nodelist;
00813 #ifdef __osf__
00814 #pragma pointer_size restore
00815 #endif
00816     int         i, j, deleted, totalDeleted;
00817     DdCache     *c;
00818     DdNode      *node,*last,*next;
00819     int         slots;
00820     long        localTime;
00821 #ifndef DD_UNSORTED_FREE_LIST
00822 #ifdef __osf__
00823 #pragma pointer_size save
00824 #pragma pointer_size short
00825 #endif
00826     DdNode      *tree;
00827 #ifdef __osf__
00828 #pragma pointer_size restore
00829 #endif
00830 #endif
00831 
00832     if (unique->deadZ == 0) {
00833         return(0);
00834     }
00835 
00836     localTime = util_cpu_time();
00837 
00838     /* If many nodes are being reclaimed, we want to resize the tables
00839     ** more aggressively, to reduce the frequency of garbage collection.
00840     */
00841     if (2.0 * unique->reclaimed > unique->allocated &&
00842         unique->slots <= unique->looseUpTo) {
00843         unique->minDead = (DD_GC_PERCENT_HI * unique->slots) / 100;
00844 #ifdef DD_VERBOSE
00845         if (unique->gcPercent == DD_GC_PERCENT_LO) {
00846             (void) fprintf(stderr,"GC percentage = %d\t", DD_GC_PERCENT_HI);
00847             (void) fprintf(stderr,"minDead = %d\n", unique->minDead);
00848         }
00849 #endif
00850         unique->gcPercent = DD_GC_PERCENT_HI;
00851     }
00852 
00853     unique->garbageCollections++;
00854 #ifdef DD_VERBOSE
00855     (void) fprintf(stderr,"garbage collecting (%d dead out of %d)...",
00856                    unique->deadZ,unique->keysZ);
00857 #endif
00858 
00859     /* Remove references to garbage collected nodes from the cache. */
00860     if (clearCache) {
00861         slots = unique->cacheSlots;
00862         for (i = 0; i < slots; i++) {
00863             c = &cache[i];
00864             if (c->data != NULL) {
00865                 if (Cudd_Regular(c->f)->ref == 0 ||
00866                 Cudd_Regular(c->g)->ref == 0 ||
00867                 Cudd_Regular(c->h)->ref == 0 ||
00868                 (c->data != DD_NON_CONSTANT &&
00869                 Cudd_Regular(c->data)->ref == 0)) {
00870                     c->data = NULL;
00871                     unique->cachedeletions++;
00872                 }
00873             }
00874         }
00875     }
00876 
00877     /* Now return dead nodes to free list. Count them for sanity check. */
00878     totalDeleted = 0;
00879 #ifndef DD_UNSORTED_FREE_LIST
00880     tree = NULL;
00881 #endif
00882 
00883     for (i = 0; i < unique->sizeZ; i++) {
00884         if (unique->subtableZ[i].dead == 0) continue;
00885         nodelist = unique->subtableZ[i].nodelist;
00886 
00887         deleted = 0;
00888         slots = unique->subtableZ[i].slots;
00889         for (j = 0; j < slots; j++) {
00890             node = nodelist[j];
00891             last = NULL;
00892             while (node != NULL) {
00893                 next = node->next;
00894                 if (node->ref == 0) {
00895                     deleted++;
00896 #ifndef DD_UNSORTED_FREE_LIST
00897 #ifdef __osf__
00898 #pragma pointer_size save
00899 #pragma pointer_size short
00900 #endif
00901                     cuddOrderedInsert(&tree,node);
00902 #ifdef DD_STATS
00903                     unique->nodesFreed++;
00904 #endif
00905 #ifdef __osf__
00906 #pragma pointer_size restore
00907 #endif
00908 #else
00909                     cuddDeallocNode(unique,node);
00910 #endif
00911                     if (last != NULL) {
00912                         last->next = next;
00913                     } else {
00914                         nodelist[j] = next;
00915                     }
00916                 } else {
00917                     last = node;
00918                 }           
00919                 node = next;
00920             }
00921         }
00922         if ((unsigned) deleted != unique->subtableZ[i].dead) {
00923             (void) fprintf(stderr,"cuddGarbageCollectZdd: problem in table %d\n",i);
00924             fail("cuddGarbageCollectZdd: dead count != deleted");
00925         }
00926         totalDeleted += deleted;
00927         unique->subtableZ[i].keys -= deleted;
00928         unique->subtableZ[i].dead = 0;
00929     }
00930 
00931     /* No need to examine the constant table for ZDDs.
00932     ** If we did we should be careful not to count whatever dead
00933     ** nodes we found there among the dead ZDD nodes. */
00934     if ((unsigned) totalDeleted != unique->deadZ) {
00935         fail("cuddGarbageCollectZdd: dead count != deleted");
00936     }
00937     unique->keysZ -= totalDeleted;
00938     unique->deadZ = 0;
00939 
00940 #ifndef DD_UNSORTED_FREE_LIST
00941     unique->nextFree = cuddOrderedThread(tree,unique->nextFree);
00942 #endif
00943 
00944     unique->GCTime += util_cpu_time() - localTime;
00945 
00946 #ifdef DD_VERBOSE
00947     (void) fprintf(stderr," done\n");
00948 #endif
00949 
00950     return(totalDeleted);
00951 
00952 } /* end of cuddGarbageCollectZdd */

01055 DdNode *
01056 cuddUniqueInter(
01057   DdManager * unique,
01058   int  index,
01059   DdNode * T,
01060   DdNode * E)
01061 {
01062     int pos;
01063     unsigned int level;
01064     int retval;
01065 #ifdef __osf__
01066 #pragma pointer_size save
01067 #pragma pointer_size short
01068 #endif
01069     DdNode **nodelist;
01070     DdNode *looking;
01071     DdSubtable *subtable;
01072 #ifdef __osf__
01073 #pragma pointer_size restore
01074 #endif
01075 
01076 #ifdef DD_UNIQUE_PROFILE
01077     unique->uniqueLookUps++;
01078 #endif
01079 
01080     if (index >= unique->size) {
01081         if (!ddResizeTable(unique,index)) return(NULL);
01082     }
01083 
01084     level = unique->perm[index];
01085     subtable = &(unique->subtables[level]);
01086 
01087 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01088     assert(level < (unsigned) cuddI(unique,T->index));
01089     assert(level < (unsigned) cuddI(unique,Cudd_Regular(E)->index));
01090 #endif
01091 
01092     pos = ddHash(T, E, subtable->shift);
01093     nodelist = subtable->nodelist;
01094     looking = nodelist[pos];
01095 
01096     while (looking != NULL) {
01097         if (cuddT(looking) == T && cuddE(looking) == E) {
01098             if (looking->ref == 0) {
01099                 cuddReclaim(unique,looking);
01100             }
01101             return(looking);
01102         }
01103         looking = looking->next;
01104 #ifdef DD_UNIQUE_PROFILE
01105         unique->uniqueLinks++;
01106 #endif
01107     }
01108 
01109     /* countDead is 0 if deads should be counted and ~0 if they should not. */
01110     if (unique->autoDyn &&
01111     unique->keys - (unique->dead & unique->countDead) >= unique->nextDyn) {
01112 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01113         retval = Cudd_DebugCheck(unique);
01114         if (retval != 0) return(NULL);
01115         retval = Cudd_CheckKeys(unique);
01116         if (retval != 0) return(NULL);
01117 #endif
01118         retval = Cudd_ReduceHeap(unique,unique->autoMethod,10); /* 10 = whatever */
01119         if (retval == 0) unique->reordered = 2;
01120 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01121         retval = Cudd_DebugCheck(unique);
01122         if (retval != 0) unique->reordered = 2;
01123         retval = Cudd_CheckKeys(unique);
01124         if (retval != 0) unique->reordered = 2;
01125 #endif
01126         return(NULL);
01127     }
01128 
01129     if (subtable->keys > subtable->maxKeys) {
01130         if (unique->gcEnabled &&
01131             ((unique->dead > unique->minDead) ||
01132             ((unique->dead > unique->minDead / 2) &&
01133             (subtable->dead > subtable->keys * 0.95)))) { /* too many dead */
01134             (void) cuddGarbageCollect(unique,1);
01135         } else {
01136             ddRehash(unique,(int)level);
01137             pos = ddHash(T, E, subtable->shift);
01138             nodelist = subtable->nodelist;
01139         }
01140     }
01141 
01142     unique->keys++;
01143     subtable->keys++;
01144 
01145     /* Ref T & E before calling cuddAllocNode, because it may garbage
01146     ** collect, and then T & E would be lost.
01147     */
01148     cuddRef(T);
01149     cuddRef(E);
01150     looking = cuddAllocNode(unique);
01151     if (looking == NULL) return(NULL);
01152     looking->ref = 0;
01153     looking->index = index;
01154     cuddT(looking) = T;
01155     cuddE(looking) = E;
01156     looking->next = nodelist[pos];
01157     nodelist[pos] = looking;
01158 
01159     return(looking);
01160 
01161 } /* end of cuddUniqueInter */

01300 DdNode *
01301 cuddUniqueConst(
01302   DdManager * unique,
01303   CUDD_VALUE_TYPE  value)
01304 {
01305     int pos;
01306 #ifdef __osf__
01307 #pragma pointer_size save
01308 #pragma pointer_size short
01309 #endif
01310     DdNode **nodelist;
01311 #ifdef __osf__
01312 #pragma pointer_size restore
01313 #endif
01314     DdNode *looking;
01315     hack split;
01316 
01317 #ifdef DD_UNIQUE_PROFILE
01318     unique->uniqueLookUps++;
01319 #endif
01320 
01321     if (unique->constants.keys > unique->constants.maxKeys) {
01322         if (unique->gcEnabled && ((unique->dead > unique->minDead) ||
01323         (10 * unique->constants.dead > 9 * unique->constants.keys))) {  /* too many dead */
01324             (void) cuddGarbageCollect(unique,1);
01325         } else {
01326             ddRehash(unique,CUDD_MAXINDEX);
01327         }
01328     }
01329 
01330     cuddAdjust(value); /* for the case of crippled infinities */
01331 
01332     if (ddAbs(value) < unique->epsilon) {
01333         value = 0.0;
01334     }
01335     split.value = value;
01336 
01337     pos = ddHash(split.bits[0], split.bits[1], unique->constants.shift);
01338     nodelist = unique->constants.nodelist;
01339     looking = nodelist[pos];
01340 
01341     /* Here we compare values both for equality and for difference less
01342      * than epsilon. The first comparison is required when values are
01343      * infinite, since Infinity - Infinity is NaN and NaN < X is 0 for
01344      * every X.
01345      */
01346     while (looking != NULL) {
01347         if (looking->type.value == value ||
01348         ddEqualVal(looking->type.value,value,unique->epsilon)) {
01349             if (looking->ref == 0) {
01350                 cuddReclaim(unique,looking);
01351             }
01352             return(looking);
01353         }
01354         looking = looking->next;
01355 #ifdef DD_UNIQUE_PROFILE
01356         unique->uniqueLinks++;
01357 #endif
01358     }
01359 
01360     unique->keys++;
01361     unique->constants.keys++;
01362 
01363     looking = cuddAllocNode(unique);
01364     looking->ref = 0;
01365     looking->index = CUDD_MAXINDEX;
01366     looking->type.value = value;
01367     looking->next = nodelist[pos];
01368     nodelist[pos] = looking;
01369 
01370     return(looking);
01371

01388 int
01389 cuddInsertSubtables(
01390   DdManager * unique,
01391   int  n,
01392   int  level)
01393 {
01394 #ifdef __osf__
01395 #pragma pointer_size save
01396 #pragma pointer_size short
01397 #endif
01398     DdSubtable *newsubtables;
01399     DdNode **newnodelist;
01400     DdNode **newvars;
01401 #ifdef __osf__
01402 #pragma pointer_size restore
01403 #endif
01404     int oldsize,newsize;
01405     int i,j,index,reorderSave;
01406     int numSlots = CUDD_UNIQUE_SLOTS;
01407     int *newperm, *newinvperm;
01408     DdNode *one, *zero;
01409 
01410 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01411     assert(n > 0 && level < unique->size);
01412 #endif
01413 
01414     oldsize = unique->size;
01415     /* Easy case: there is still room in the current table. */
01416     if (oldsize + n <= unique->maxSize) {
01417         /* Shift the tables at and below level. */
01418         for (i = oldsize - 1; i >= level; i--) {
01419             unique->subtables[i+n].slots    = unique->subtables[i].slots;
01420             unique->subtables[i+n].shift    = unique->subtables[i].shift;
01421             unique->subtables[i+n].keys     = unique->subtables[i].keys;
01422             unique->subtables[i+n].maxKeys  = unique->subtables[i].maxKeys;
01423             unique->subtables[i+n].dead     = unique->subtables[i].dead;
01424             unique->subtables[i+n].nodelist = unique->subtables[i].nodelist;
01425             index                           = unique->invperm[i];
01426             unique->invperm[i+n]            = index;
01427             unique->perm[index]            += n;
01428         }
01429         /* Create new subtables. */
01430         for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
01431             unique->subtables[level+i].slots = numSlots;
01432             unique->subtables[level+i].shift = sizeof(int) * 8 -
01433                 cuddComputeFloorLog2(numSlots);
01434             unique->subtables[level+i].keys = 0;
01435             unique->subtables[level+i].maxKeys = numSlots * DD_MAX_SUBTABLE_DENSITY;
01436             unique->subtables[level+i].dead = 0;
01437             unique->perm[oldsize+i] = level + i;
01438             unique->invperm[level+i] = oldsize + i;
01439 #ifdef __osf__
01440 #pragma pointer_size save
01441 #pragma pointer_size short
01442 #endif
01443             newnodelist = unique->subtables[level+i].nodelist = ALLOC(DdNode *, numSlots);
01444 #ifdef __osf__
01445 #pragma pointer_size restore
01446 #endif
01447             if (newnodelist == NULL) {
01448                 unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
01449                 return(0);
01450             }
01451             for (j = 0; j < numSlots; j++) {
01452                 newnodelist[j] = NULL;
01453             }
01454         }
01455     } else {
01456         /* The current table is too small: we need to allocate a new,
01457         ** larger one; move all old subtables, and initialize the new
01458         ** subtables.
01459         */
01460         newsize = oldsize + n + DD_DEFAULT_RESIZE;
01461 #ifdef DD_VERBOSE
01462         (void) fprintf(stderr,"Increasing the table size from %d to %d\n",
01463             unique->maxSize, newsize);
01464 #endif
01465         newsubtables = ALLOC(DdSubtable,newsize);
01466         if (newsubtables == NULL) {
01467             unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
01468             return(0);
01469         }
01470 #ifdef __osf__
01471 #pragma pointer_size save
01472 #pragma pointer_size short
01473 #endif
01474         newvars = ALLOC(DdNode *,newsize);
01475 #ifdef __osf__
01476 #pragma pointer_size restore
01477 #endif
01478         if (newvars == NULL) {
01479             unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
01480             return(0);
01481         }
01482         newperm = ALLOC(int,newsize);
01483         if (newperm == NULL) {
01484             unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
01485             return(0);
01486         }
01487         newinvperm = ALLOC(int,newsize);
01488         if (newinvperm == NULL) {
01489             unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
01490             return(0);
01491         }
01492         unique->memused += (newsize - unique->maxSize) * ((numSlots+1) *
01493             sizeof(DdNode *) + 2 * sizeof(int) + sizeof(DdSubtable));
01494         for (i = 0; i < level; i++) {
01495             newsubtables[i].slots = unique->subtables[i].slots;
01496             newsubtables[i].shift = unique->subtables[i].shift;
01497             newsubtables[i].keys = unique->subtables[i].keys;
01498             newsubtables[i].maxKeys = unique->subtables[i].maxKeys;
01499             newsubtables[i].dead = unique->subtables[i].dead;
01500             newsubtables[i].nodelist = unique->subtables[i].nodelist;
01501             newvars[i] = unique->vars[i];
01502             newperm[i] = unique->perm[i];
01503             newinvperm[i] = unique->invperm[i];
01504         }
01505         for (i = level; i < oldsize; i++) {
01506             newperm[i] = unique->perm[i];
01507         }
01508         for (i = level; i < level + n; i++) {
01509             newsubtables[i].slots = numSlots;
01510             newsubtables[i].shift = sizeof(int) * 8 -
01511                 cuddComputeFloorLog2(numSlots);
01512             newsubtables[i].keys = 0;
01513             newsubtables[i].maxKeys = numSlots * DD_MAX_SUBTABLE_DENSITY;
01514             newsubtables[i].dead = 0;
01515             newperm[oldsize + i - level] = i;
01516             newinvperm[i] = oldsize + i - level;
01517 #ifdef __osf__
01518 #pragma pointer_size save
01519 #pragma pointer_size short
01520 #endif
01521             newnodelist = newsubtables[i].nodelist = ALLOC(DdNode *, numSlots);
01522 #ifdef __osf__
01523 #pragma pointer_size restore
01524 #endif
01525             if (newnodelist == NULL) {
01526                 unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
01527                 return(0);
01528             }
01529             for (j = 0; j < numSlots; j++) {
01530                 newnodelist[j] = NULL;
01531             }
01532         }
01533         for (i = level; i < oldsize; i++) {
01534             newsubtables[i+n].slots    = unique->subtables[i].slots;
01535             newsubtables[i+n].shift    = unique->subtables[i].shift;
01536             newsubtables[i+n].keys     = unique->subtables[i].keys;
01537             newsubtables[i+n].maxKeys  = unique->subtables[i].maxKeys;
01538             newsubtables[i+n].dead     = unique->subtables[i].dead;
01539             newsubtables[i+n].nodelist = unique->subtables[i].nodelist;
01540             newvars[i]                 = unique->vars[i];
01541             index                      = unique->invperm[i];
01542             newinvperm[i+n]            = index;
01543             newperm[index]            += n;
01544         }
01545         FREE(unique->subtables);
01546         unique->subtables = newsubtables;
01547         unique->maxSize = newsize;
01548         FREE(unique->vars);
01549         unique->vars = newvars;
01550         FREE(unique->perm);

01561 #ifdef __osf__

01563 #endif

01565                 unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;

01569             unique->memused +=
01570                 (newsize - ddMax(unique->maxSize,unique->maxSizeZ))
01571                 * sizeof(DdNode *);
01572         }
01573 
01574     }
01575     unique->slots += n * numSlots;
01576     ddFixLimits(unique);
01577     unique->size += n;
01578 
01579     /* Now that the table is in a coherent state, create the new
01580     ** projection functions. We need to temporarily disable reordering,
01581     ** because we cannot reorder without projection functions in place.
01582     **/
01583     one = unique->one;
01584     zero = Cudd_Not(one);
01585 
01586     reorderSave = unique->autoDyn;
01587     unique->autoDyn = 0;
01588     for (i = oldsize; i < oldsize + n; i++) {
01589         unique->vars[i] = cuddUniqueInter(unique,i,one,zero);
01590         if (unique->vars[i] == NULL) {
01591             unique->autoDyn = reorderSave;
01592             return(0);
01593         }
01594         cuddRef(unique->vars[i]);
01595     }
01596     if (unique->tree != NULL) {
01597         unique->tree->size += n;
01598         unique->tree->index = unique->invperm[0];
01599         ddPatchTree(unique,unique->tree);
01600     }
01601     unique->autoDyn = reorderSave;
01602 
01603     return(1);
01604

01622 int
01623 cuddDestroySubtables(
01624   DdManager * unique,
01625   int  n)
01626 {
01627 #ifdef __osf__
01628 #pragma pointer_size save
01629 #pragma pointer_size short
01630 #endif
01631     DdSubtable *subtables;
01632     DdNode **nodelist;
01633     DdNode **vars;
01634 #ifdef __osf__
01635 #pragma pointer_size restore
01636 #endif
01637     int firstIndex, lastIndex;
01638     int index, level, newlevel;
01639     int lowestLevel;
01640     int shift;
01641     int found;
01642 
01643     /* Sanity check and set up. */
01644     if (n <= 0) return(0);
01645 
01646     subtables = unique->subtables;
01647     vars = unique->vars;
01648     firstIndex = unique->size - n;
01649     lastIndex  = unique->size - 1;
01650 
01651     /* Check for nodes labeled by the variables being destroyed
01652     ** that may still be in use.  It is allowed to destroy a variable
01653     ** only if there are no such nodes. Also, find the lowest level
01654     ** among the variables being destroyed. This will make further
01655     ** processing more efficient.
01656     */
01657     lowestLevel = unique->size;
01658     for (index = firstIndex; index < lastIndex; index++) {
01659         level = unique->perm[index];
01660         if (level < lowestLevel) lowestLevel = level;
01661         nodelist = subtables[level].nodelist;
01662         if (subtables[level].keys - subtables[level].dead != 1) return(0);
01663         /* The projection function should be isolated. If the ref count
01664         ** is 1, everything is OK. If the ref count is saturated, then
01665         ** we need to make sure that there are no nodes pointing to it.
01666         ** As for the external references, we assume the application is
01667         ** responsible for them.
01668         */
01669         if (vars[index]->ref != 1) {
01670             if (vars[index]->ref != DD_MAXREF) return(0);
01671             found = cuddFindParent(unique,vars[index]);
01672             if (found) {
01673                 return(0);
01674             } else {
01675                 vars[index]->ref = 1;
01676             }
01677         }
01678         Cudd_RecursiveDeref(unique,vars[index]);
01679     }
01680 
01681     /* Collect garbage, because we cannot afford having dead nodes pointing
01682     ** to the dead nodes in the subtables being destroyed.
01683     */
01684     (void) cuddGarbageCollect(unique,1);
01685 
01686     /* Here we know we can destroy our subtables. */
01687     for (index = firstIndex; index < lastIndex; index++) {
01688         level = unique->perm[index];
01689         nodelist = subtables[level].nodelist;
01690 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01691         assert(subtables[level].keys == 0);
01692 #endif
01693         FREE(nodelist);
01694         unique->memused -= subtables[level].slots;
01695         unique->slots -= subtables[level].slots;
01696         unique->dead -= unique[level].dead;
01697         unique->keys--;
01698     }
01699 
01700     /* Here all subtables to be destroyed have their keys field == 0 and
01701     ** their hash tables have been freed.
01702     ** We now scan the subtables from level lowestLevel + 1 to level size - 1,
01703     ** shifting the subtables as required. We keep a running count of
01704     ** how many subtables have been moved, so that we know by how many
01705     ** positions each subtable should be shifted.
01706     */
01707     shift = 1;
01708     for (level = lowestLevel + 1; level < unique->size; level++) {
01709         if (subtables[level].keys == 0) {
01710             shift++;
01711             continue;
01712         }
01713         newlevel = level - shift;
01714         subtables[newlevel].slots = subtables[level].slots;
01715         subtables[newlevel].shift = subtables[level].shift;
01716         subtables[newlevel].keys = subtables[level].keys;
01717         subtables[newlevel].maxKeys = subtables[level].maxKeys;
01718         subtables[newlevel].dead = subtables[level].dead;
01719         subtables[newlevel].nodelist = subtables[level].nodelist;
01720         unique->invperm[newlevel]  = unique->invperm[level];
01721     }
01722 
01723     unique->size -= n;
01724 
01725     return(1);
01726 
01727 } /* end of cuddDestroySubtables */

01816             unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
01817             return(0);

01856             newsubtables[i].dead = 0;

01858             newinvperm[i] = i;
01859 #ifdef __osf__
01860 #pragma pointer_size save
01861 #pragma pointer_size short
01862 #endif
01863             newnodelist = newsubtables[i].nodelist = ALLOC(DdNode *, numSlots);
01864 #ifdef __osf__
01865 #pragma pointer_size restore
01866 #endif
01867             if (newnodelist == NULL) {
01868                 unique->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
01869                 return(0);
01870             }
01871             for (j = 0; j < numSlots; j++) {
01872                 newnodelist[j] = NULL;
01873             }
01874         }
01875         FREE(unique->subtableZ);
01876         unique->subtableZ = newsubtables;

01884     ddFixLimits(unique);
01885     unique->sizeZ = index + 1;
01886 
01887     /* Now that the table is in a coherent state, update the ZDD
01888     ** universe. We need to temporarily disable reordering,
01889     ** because we cannot reorder without universe in place.
01890     */
01891     one = unique->one;
01892     zero = unique->zero;
01893 
01894     reorderSave = unique->autoDynZ;

01898         unique->autoDynZ = reorderSave;

01923 static void
01924 ddRehash(
01925   DdManager * unique,
01926   int  i)
01927 {
01928     unsigned int slots, oldslots;
01929     int shift, oldshift;
01930     int j, pos;
01931 #ifdef __osf__
01932 #pragma pointer_size save
01933 #pragma pointer_size short
01934 #endif
01935     DdNode **nodelist, **oldnodelist;
01936 #ifdef __osf__
01937 #pragma pointer_size restore
01938 #endif
01939     DdNode *node, *next;
01940     hack split;
01941     extern void (*MMoutOfMemory)(long);
01942     void (*saveHandler)(long);
01943 
01944     if (2.0 * unique->reclaimed <= unique->allocated ||
01945         unique->slots > unique->looseUpTo) {
01946         unique->minDead = (DD_GC_PERCENT_LO * unique->slots) / 100;
01947 #ifdef DD_VERBOSE
01948         if (unique->gcPercent == DD_GC_PERCENT_HI) {
01949             (void) fprintf(stderr,"GC percentage = %d\t", DD_GC_PERCENT_LO);
01950             (void) fprintf(stderr,"minDead = %d\n", unique->minDead);
01951         }
01952 #endif
01953         unique->gcPercent = DD_GC_PERCENT_LO;
01954     }
01955 
01956     if (i != CUDD_MAXINDEX) {
01957         oldslots = unique->subtables[i].slots;
01958         oldshift = unique->subtables[i].shift;
01959         oldnodelist = unique->subtables[i].nodelist;
01960 
01961         /* Compute the new size of the subtable. Normally, we just
01962         ** double.  However, after reordering, a table may be severely
01963         ** overloaded. Therefore, we iterate. */
01964         slots = oldslots;
01965         shift = oldshift;
01966         do {
01967             slots <<= 1;
01968             shift--;
01969         } while (slots * DD_MAX_SUBTABLE_DENSITY <
01970                  2 * unique->subtables[i].keys);
01971 
01972         saveHandler = MMoutOfMemory;
01973         MMoutOfMemory = Cudd_OutOfMem;
01974 #ifdef __osf__
01975 #pragma pointer_size save
01976 #pragma pointer_size short
01977 #endif
01978         nodelist = ALLOC(DdNode *, slots);
01979 #ifdef __osf__
01980 #pragma pointer_size restore
01981 #endif
01982         MMoutOfMemory = saveHandler;
01983         if (nodelist == NULL) {
01984             int j;
01985             (void) fprintf(stderr,
01986                            "Unable to resize subtable %d for lack of memory\n",
01987                            i);
01988             /* Prevent frequent resizing attempts. */
01989             cuddGarbageCollect(unique,1);
01990             for (j = 0; j < unique->size; j++) {
01991                 unique->subtables[j].maxKeys <<= 1;
01992             }
01993             unique->constants.maxKeys <<= 1;
01994             return;
01995         }
01996         unique->subtables[i].nodelist = nodelist;
01997         unique->subtables[i].slots = slots;
01998         unique->subtables[i].shift = shift;
01999         unique->subtables[i].maxKeys = slots * DD_MAX_SUBTABLE_DENSITY;
02000 
02001         for (j = 0; (unsigned) j < slots; j++) {
02002             nodelist[j] = NULL;
02003         }
02004         for (j = 0; (unsigned) j < oldslots; j++) {
02005             node = oldnodelist[j];
02006             while (node != NULL) {
02007                 next = node->next;
02008                 pos = ddHash(cuddT(node), cuddE(node), shift);
02009                 node->next = nodelist[pos];
02010                 nodelist[pos] = node;
02011                 node = next;
02012             }
02013         }
02014         FREE(oldnodelist);
02015 
02016 #ifdef DD_VERBOSE
02017         (void) fprintf(stderr,"rehashing layer %d: keys %d dead %d new size %d\n",
02018         i,unique->subtables[i].keys,unique->subtables[i].dead,slots);
02019 #endif
02020     } else {
02021         oldslots = unique->constants.slots;
02022         oldshift = unique->constants.shift;
02023         oldnodelist = unique->constants.nodelist;
02024 
02025         /* The constant subtable is never subjected to reordering.
02026         ** Therefore, when it is resized, it is because it has just
02027         ** reached the maximum load. We can safely just double the size,
02028         ** with no need for the loop we use for the other tables.
02029         */
02030         slots = oldslots << 1;
02031         shift = oldshift - 1;
02032         saveHandler = MMoutOfMemory;
02033         MMoutOfMemory = Cudd_OutOfMem;
02034 #ifdef __osf__
02035 #pragma pointer_size save
02036 #pragma pointer_size short
02037 #endif
02038         nodelist = ALLOC(DdNode *, slots);
02039 #ifdef __osf__
02040 #pragma pointer_size restore
02041 #endif
02042         MMoutOfMemory = saveHandler;
02043         if (nodelist == NULL) {
02044             int j;
02045             (void) fprintf(stderr,
02046                            "Unable to resize constant subtable for lack of memory\n");
02047             cuddGarbageCollect(unique,1);
02048             for (j = 0; j < unique->size; j++) {
02049                 unique->subtables[j].maxKeys <<= 1;
02050             }
02051             unique->constants.maxKeys <<= 1;
02052             return;
02053         }
02054         unique->constants.slots = slots;
02055         unique->constants.shift = shift;
02056         unique->constants.maxKeys = slots * DD_MAX_SUBTABLE_DENSITY;
02057         unique->constants.nodelist = nodelist;
02058         for (j = 0; (unsigned) j < slots; j++) {
02059             nodelist[j] = NULL;
02060         }
02061         for (j = 0; (unsigned) j < oldslots; j++) {
02062             node = oldnodelist[j];
02063             while (node != NULL) {
02064                 next = node->next;
02065                 split.value = cuddV(node);
02066                 pos = ddHash(split.bits[0], split.bits[1], shift);
02067                 node->next = nodelist[pos];
02068                 nodelist[pos] = node;
02069                 node = next;
02070             }
02071         }
02072         FREE(oldnodelist);
02073 
02074 #ifdef DD_VERBOSE
02075         (void) fprintf(stderr,"rehashing constants: keys %d dead %d new size %d\n",
02076         unique->constants.keys,unique->constants.dead,slots);
02077 #endif
02078     }
02079 
02080     /* Update global data */
02081 
02082     unique->memused += (slots - oldslots) * sizeof(DdNode *);
02083     unique->slots += (slots - oldslots);
02084     ddFixLimits(unique);
02085 
02086 } /* end of ddRehash */

02373     ** because we cannot reorder without projection functions in place.

02488 static void
02489 cuddOrderedInsert(
02490   DdNode ** root,
02491   DdNode * node)
02492 {
02493     DdNode *scan;
02494     DdNode **scanP;
02495     DdNode **stack[DD_STACK_SIZE];
02496     int stackN = 0;

02500         stack[stackN++] = scanP;
02501         if (DD_INSERT_COMPARE(node, scan) == 0) { /* add to page list */
02502             DD_NEXT(node) = DD_NEXT(scan);
02503             DD_NEXT(scan) = node;
02504             return;
02505         }
02506         scanP = (node < scan) ? &DD_LEFT(scan) : &DD_RIGHT(scan);
02507     }
02508     DD_RIGHT(node) = DD_LEFT(node) = DD_NEXT(node) = NULL;
02509     DD_COLOR(node) = DD_RED;
02510     *scanP = node;
02511     stack[stackN] = &node;

02537 static DdNode *
02538 cuddOrderedThread(
02539   DdNode * root,
02540   DdNode * list)
02541 {
02542     DdNode *current, *next, *prev, *end;
02543 
02544     current = root;
02545     /* The first word in the node is used to implement a stack that holds
02546     ** the nodes from the root of the tree to the current node. Here we
02547     ** put the root of the tree at the bottom of the stack.
02548     */
02549     *((DdNode **) current) = NULL;
02550 
02551     while (current != NULL) {
02552         if (DD_RIGHT(current) != NULL) {
02553             /* If possible, we follow the "right" link. Eventually we'll
02554             ** find the node with the largest address in the current tree.
02555             ** In this phase we use the first word of a node to implemen
02556             ** a stack of the nodes on the path from the root to "current".
02557             ** Also, we disconnect the "right" pointers to indicate that
02558             ** we have already followed them.
02559             */
02560             next = DD_RIGHT(current);
02561             DD_RIGHT(current) = NULL;
02562             *((DdNode **)next) = current;
02563             current = next;
02564         } else {
02565             /* We can't proceed along the "right" links any further.
02566             ** Hence "current" is the largest element in the current tree.
02567             ** We make this node the new head of "list". (Repeating this
02568             ** operation until the tree is empty yields the desired linear
02569             ** threading of all nodes.)
02570             */
02571             prev = *((DdNode **) current); /* save prev node on stack in prev */
02572             /* Traverse the linked list of current until the end. */
02573             for (end = current; DD_NEXT(end) != NULL; end = DD_NEXT(end));
02574             DD_NEXT(end) = list; /* attach "list" at end and make */
02575             list = current;   /* "current" the new head of "list" */
02576             /* Now, if current has a "left" child, we push it on the stack.
02577             ** Otherwise, we just continue with the parent of "current".
02578             */
02579             if (DD_LEFT(current) != NULL) {
02580                 next = DD_LEFT(current);
02581                 *((DdNode **) next) = prev;
02582                 current = next;
02583             } else {
02584                 current = prev;
02585             }
02586         }
02587     }
02588 
02589     return(list);
02590 
02591 } /* end of cuddOrderedThread */

02657 static void
02658 cuddDoRebalance(
02659   DdNode *** stack,
02660   int  stackN)
02661 {
02662     DdNode **xP, *x, *y, **parentP, *parent, **grandpaP, *grandpa;
02663 
02664     xP = stack[stackN];
02665     x = *xP;
02666     /* Work our way back up, re-balancing the tree. */
02667     while (--stackN >= 0) {
02668         parentP = stack[stackN];
02669         parent = *parentP;
02670         if (DD_IS_BLACK(parent)) break;
02671         /* Since the root is black, here a non-null grandparent exists. */
02672         grandpaP = stack[stackN-1];
02673         grandpa = *grandpaP;
02674         if (parent == DD_LEFT(grandpa)) {
02675             y = DD_RIGHT(grandpa);
02676             if (y != NULL && DD_IS_RED(y)) {
02677                 DD_COLOR(parent) = DD_BLACK;
02678                 DD_COLOR(y) = DD_BLACK;
02679                 DD_COLOR(grandpa) = DD_RED;
02680                 x = grandpa;
02681                 stackN--;
02682             } else {
02683                 if (x == DD_RIGHT(parent)) {
02684                     cuddRotateLeft(parentP);
02685                     DD_COLOR(x) = DD_BLACK;
02686                 } else {
02687                     DD_COLOR(parent) = DD_BLACK;
02688                 }
02689                 DD_COLOR(grandpa) = DD_RED;
02690                 cuddRotateRight(grandpaP);
02691                 break;
02692             }
02693         } else {
02694             y = DD_LEFT(grandpa);
02695             if (y != NULL && DD_IS_RED(y)) {
02696                 DD_COLOR(parent) = DD_BLACK;
02697                 DD_COLOR(y) = DD_BLACK;
02698                 DD_COLOR(grandpa) = DD_RED;
02699                 x = grandpa;
02700                 stackN--;
02701             } else {
02702                 if (x == DD_LEFT(parent)) {
02703                     cuddRotateRight(parentP);
02704                     DD_COLOR(x) = DD_BLACK;
02705                 } else {
02706                     DD_COLOR(parent) = DD_BLACK;
02707                 }
02708                 DD_COLOR(grandpa) = DD_RED;
02709                 cuddRotateLeft(grandpaP);
02710             }
02711         }
02712     }
02713     DD_COLOR(*(stack[0])) = DD_BLACK;
02714 
02715 } /* end of cuddDoRebalance */
